        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Eukaryotic-type DNA polymerase involved in viral genomic replication. DNA synthesis is protein primed, and acts in a strand displacement replication. Assembles in complex with viral pTP, DBP, host NFIA and host POU2F1/OCT1 on viral origin of replication. The polymerase covalently transfers dCMP onto pTP, thereby initiating complementary strand synthesis"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
